-- All but one of major U.S. banks meet Fed's stress test hurdle
-- By Emily Stephenson
-- Thu Mar 20, 2014 04:00PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, March 20 (Reuters) - U.S. banks generally have big enough capital buffers to withstand a drastic economic downturn, the Federal Reserve said on Thursday, announcing that 29 out of 30 major banks met the minimum hurdle in its annual health check.

